dollars, of $24 056. Probabilistic sensitivity analysis suggested intensive BP 
treatment would be cost-effective compared with standard treatment 86.7% of the 
time at a willingness-to-pay threshold of $$60 000 per QALY.
CONCLUSION: The result of this study showed that intensive BP treatment appears 
to be a cost-effective choice for patients with a high risk of CVD in Saudi 
Arabia when compared with standard treatment.

